Notes: Column A is an arbitrary index number (or text label) of the point to be processed
Column B is the depth at that point (cm)
Column C is the velocity at that point (cm/s)
Column D is bed roughness height (cm) for a log velocity profile
Column E is fork length (cm); is ignored unless mass is also specified
Column F is mass (g); is ignored unless fork length is also specified
Column G is for temperature in degrees C
Column H is turbidity in NTU
Column I is the address for the drift density CSV file
Columns D-I are optional, but don't delete the columns or their headers; just leave the cells blank if you don't want to specify them
If you leave an optional column blank, it will default to the values specified on the Model Settings tab
